The major global manufacturers of Dried Chilli Powder include Raj Masala, Ahirkar international, Synthite Industries Ltd, Swani Spice, Supreme, Akay Spices, Kotanyi, Gansu Yasheng, and Cuihong, among others. In 2023, the world's top three vendors accounted for approximately 3.6% of the revenue.
Dried chilli powder is a spice made from dried and ground chili peppers. It is a popular ingredient in many cuisines around the world, adding heat, color, and flavor to dishes. Dried chilli powder can be made from a variety of chili peppers, such as cayenne, jalapeño, and habanero, each with its own unique flavor profile and level of spiciness. The powder is typically made by drying the peppers, removing the stems and seeds, and grinding the peppers into a fine powder.This report aims to provide a comprehensive presentation of the global market for Dried Chilli Powder, with both quantitative and qualitative analysis, to help readers develop business/growth strategies, assess the market competitive situation, analyze their position in the current marketplace, and make informed business decisions regarding Dried Chilli Powder.
